INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (3,1635,'Ellie Krantz','ehkrantz@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.whyzero.com','92.251.101.197','2014-11-16 20:59:10','2014-11-16 20:59:10','I love the inspiration and ethos behind The Road and 48 minutes - it\'s all too true.. downtime and creating space for reflection and creativity are often put on the back burner amidst the hustle and bustle of life. Great post Neil, I\'ll let you know how I get on with my 48 minutes! :-) Ellie',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_7_5) AppleWebKit/537.78.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/6.1.6 Safari/537.78.2','',0,0),(8,1635,'Benaifar','benaifar@gmail.com','','61.12.61.122','2014-11-17 10:30:34','2014-11-17 10:30:34','Great initiative! I am going to do this as soon as I go one leave :D',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/38.0.2125.111 Safari/537.36','',0,0),(14,1635,'Natalie Livings','natalie.livings@YSC.com','','120.149.224.150','2014-11-20 10:34:06','2014-11-20 10:34:06','48 minutes - what a great and catchy idea Neil, founded of course in psychological research :-)  I had an interesting first 48 minutes yesterday and have sent you an email to share the experience!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko','',0,0),(18,1858,'chee-hsing pinchen','chee-hsing.pinchen@ysc.com','','203.134.159.210','2014-11-27 02:41:32','2014-11-27 02:41:32','Brilliant, such a fluid poem, captures the essence of time and space, love it!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko','',0,0),(20,1894,'Chee-Hsing Pinchen','chpinchen@gmail.com','','101.170.85.67','2014-11-27 10:05:53','2014-11-27 10:05:53','Brilliant, such a fluid poem, captures the essence of time and space, love it!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (iPad; CPU OS 8_1_1 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/600.1.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Mobile/12B435 [FBAN/FBIOS;FBAV/18.1.0.14.11;FBBV/5295262;FBDV/iPad4,2;FBMD/iPad;FBSN/iPhone OS;FBSV/8.1.1;FBSS/2; FBCR/;FBID/tablet;FBLC/en_GB;FBOP/1]','',0,0),(21,1635,'Agata','Agata@agataphotography.co.uk','http://www.agataphotography.co.uk','82.44.233.96','2014-11-27 16:10:54','2014-11-27 16:10:54','What an inspiring idea Neil! Even though I work as a creative (I\'m a photographer) I find it is still easy to forget to nourish my creative side. Shooting for others, as much as I love it, doesn\'t always  allow me to push boundaries and try new things. I\'ll use 48 minutes as my creative challenge and report back on what happened!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (iPad; CPU OS 7_1_1 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/537.51.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Mobile/11D201 [FBAN/FBIOS;FBAV/18.1.0.14.11;FBBV/5295262;FBDV/iPad4,5;FBMD/iPad;FBSN/iPhone OS;FBSV/7.1.1;FBSS/2; FBCR/Three;FBID/tablet;FBLC/en_GB;FBOP/1]','',0,0),(23,1894,'Rosie','Elgastor01@gmail.com','','94.9.174.28','2014-11-29 09:37:30','2014-11-29 09:37:30','excellent!! I love this!! I got totally caught up in it-the initial rush-which is how I usually feel every day!!! And then a wonderful calm sigh at the end-where I allowed myself to imagine the warm sun and the relaxing breeze...and accept that time does pass by quickly but there\'s nothing you can do to stop it so you have to enjoy and go with the moment instead... I will think of this poem in my frenzie and remind myself that I don\'t give a 48 minutes how many are left...!! I love love love that ending xx',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; CPU iPhone OS 8_1 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/600.1.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0 Mobile/12B411 Safari/600.1.4','',0,0),(50,1635,'Brittany','brittanylglenn22@hotmail.com','http://allthatescapesus.com','24.49.106.85','2014-12-17 08:55:29','2014-12-17 13:55:29','This is a truly wonderful idea! As a mother of 3 it\'s so easy to neglect the opportunities to truly connect with ones self. I will use my 48 minutes to completely unwind and self indulge in my passions. Thank you for sharing!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64; rv:34.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/34.0','',0,0),(51,1635,'Bound to Eternity','boundtoeternity@gmail.com','http://www.boundtoeternity.theblogpress.com','64.183.241.130','2014-12-17 08:59:13','2014-12-17 13:59:13','Brilliant idea! I will be implementing and sharing! Thanks for the inspiring share :)\r\n\r\n- in love &amp; light eternally',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:34.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/34.0','',0,0),(53,2044,'Natalie Livings','natalie.livings@YSC.com','','198.143.37.1','2014-12-22 01:03:15','2014-12-22 06:03:15','I love your story Kyle; very inspiring to all of us who have a dream.  Well done for persevering away at it and making your dream happen!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko','',0,0),(55,1635,'Neka','wilson.neka@gmail.com','','198.143.37.1','2014-12-24 11:06:10','2014-12-24 16:06:10','I am in love with this concept Neil.  Time often escapes us and it’s great when we are reminded and encouraged to indulge others of our thoughts, inhibitions, questions, and skived ideas, fleshing out what is of value to us in our quest towards fulfillment.  Can’t wait to take a stab at this over the holiday.   \r\n\r\nWarm Regards, \r\n\r\nNeka',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 9.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/5.0)','',0,0),(56,2079,'don minnick','efltwr@att.net','','198.143.37.1','2014-12-28 13:06:33','2014-12-28 18:06:33','Hi Neil,\r\nMaybe you could consider a version of this.... Rebecca and I have built a small non-profit:  \'Wimberley Valley Artists Support Fund\', designed to help emerging and talented artists (of which there are many in our community) pay essential bills that they may be struggling with so that they can keep their focus on what they do - create great art, If an artist needs some temporary funds to pay an electric bill, buy art supplies, place their work in a show etc., we have a board of artists, gallery owners and patrons who vet the requests and award the money. It\'s amazing how such a small gift can make a difference in continuing an artist\'s flow. Thanks for all that you and the Road Gallery are already doing for art and artists.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko','',0,0),(57,2079,'Neil Jacobs','neil@theroadgallery.com','http://localhost','198.143.37.33','2015-01-02 09:51:45','2015-01-02 14:51:45','Hi Don, thanks so much for sharing this fantastic idea with me. You guys are great and I can imagine it makes a really big difference. Happy new year to you and Rebecca. Neil',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_10_1) AppleWebKit/600.2.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0.2 Safari/600.2.5','',56,2),(60,2157,'Jon Taylor','artman.taylor@gmail.com','http://www.taylorarthouse.com','198.143.41.1','2015-01-16 20:53:58','2015-01-17 01:53:58','Love your work and investigation on digital art. A couple of years ago I worked with a very talented Chinese retail mixed use designer in Bellevue, Washington in the States. She worked in the USA for about two months then would travel to present design work all around China for about 2 weeks. She had an IPad and her husband found her several sketching programs for the tablet. She sketched beautifully on paper with markers and pens. She seemed to lose none of the power of her ideas about design on the tablet. Will follow you on Instagram. Keep it going.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; CPU iPhone OS 7_1_2 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/537.51.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/7.0 Mobile/11D257 Safari/9537.53','',0,0),(62,2157,'ingeborgpompen','ingepompen@gmail.com','','198.143.41.97','2015-01-21 08:53:21','2015-01-21 13:53:21','Nice story Jon, thank you very much for sharing.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 4.4.2; SM-P900 Build/KOT49H) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/39.0.2171.93 Safari/537.36','',0,0),(67,2248,'Tony Gordon','Tg@tonygordon.biz','http://Www.tonygordon.biz','198.143.38.33','2015-01-27 13:02:18','2015-01-27 18:02:18','I am Miriam\'s dad, good to know I influenced her good taste in art.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (iPad; CPU OS 8_0 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/600.1.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0 Mobile/12A365 Safari/600.1.4','',0,0),(81,1894,'Malerie','6vonz2prce@outlook.com','http://beildho.com','198.143.41.97','2015-03-26 03:34:56','2015-03-26 07:34:56','Gosh, I wish I would have had that information earlier!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/40.0.2214.111 Safari/537.36','',0,0),(87,1635,'Luis A. Marrero','Luis@bostonimp.com','http://www.bostonimp.com','198.143.38.65','2015-04-02 23:13:38','2015-04-03 03:13:38','Wonderful concept, Neil! And I am happy for you that you are finding a meaningful path that fulfills you. Thanks for sharing.\r\n\r\nI am fortunate to have the time and space to do my creative work, spend time with those I love, and to stay connected with dear friends and associates. Life has been good to me. Thanks again!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64; Trident/7.0; TNJB; rv:11.0) like Gecko','',0,0),(88,2157,'tim','farfromhomein@yahoo.com','','198.143.37.97','2015-04-05 09:19:12','2015-04-05 13:19:12','Excellent!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 4.4.4; SM-G900V Build/KTU84P) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/41.0.2272.96 Mobile Safari/537.36','',0,0),(89,1635,'Lynne Rutherford','lynne.rutherford@brambles.com','','198.143.37.33','2015-04-09 08:11:25','2015-04-09 12:11:25','What a lovely way to stay in touch. On Tuesday I got home after a 55 minute drive on the M25 (London), and it was a beautiful spring evening. I put on a tracksuit, poured a glass of white wine and sat outside for an hour just listening to the blackbirds and songthrushes singing in the field behind our house. Pure bliss and very energising. The key is to leave the IPhone with facebook and emails inside out of reach and do nothing.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; WOW64; Trident/7.0; Touch; rv:11.0) like Gecko','',0,0),(90,2936,'Sara J','sarajohnsonjackson@gmail.com','','198.143.37.65','2015-04-10 06:44:08','2015-04-10 10:44:08','Ooh I love this interview. So interesting about both Melissa and Neil and so relevant to my place in the world right now. All power to you both!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; CPU iPhone OS 8_2 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/600.1.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0 Mobile/12D508 Safari/600.1.4','',0,0),(91,2936,'Neil Jacobs','neil@theroadgallery.com','http://localhost','198.143.37.33','2015-04-10 09:51:28','2015-04-10 13:51:28','Thanks Sara! Power to you too',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_10_1) AppleWebKit/600.2.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0.2 Safari/600.2.5','',0,2),(92,1635,'Neil Jacobs','neil@theroadgallery.com','http://localhost','198.143.37.33','2015-04-10 09:54:08','2015-04-10 13:54:08','Thanks everyone for all your great comments. We love hearing what you are doing with your 48 Minutes and are so glad it\'s resonating with you. Lynne, your evening of peace and serenity sounds delightful.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_10_1) AppleWebKit/600.2.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0.2 Safari/600.2.5','',0,2);
