 Express or Discovery card.\r\nPayees will receive an email confirmation of their transaction.\r\nOnce a payment has been made to the gift registry, no refunds will be given.\r\nGift registry credit will be held securely in The Road Gallery\'s business account until it is redeemed.\r\nGift registry credit is redeemable only at The Road Gallery.\r\nThere is no expiration date on gift registry credit. Gift registry credit cannot be redeemed for cash.\r\n\r\n<strong>Privacy Policy</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Road Gallery does not sell, rent, exchange or otherwise disclose information about our site visitors, except when compelled by law.\r\nWe collect your information in two places on the site: our mailing list and our gift registry.\r\nWe use the information you provide when you sign up to the mailing list to send you our e-newsletter which contains updates about the gallery. We will not bombard you with newsletters or other e-correspondence. On average, we send out a newsletter every 6 weeks.  You can unsubscribe from the newsletters by clicking on the unsubscribe link at the bottom of any of our newsletters.\r\nInformation you provide on the gift registry is used to set up your gift registry, or, if you are giving a gift to the registry, we use your information to process card transactions. Also, see gift registry terms and conditions above about the message you leave and the amount you give.\r\nUsing Google Analytics, we also automatically collect some aggregate data about visitors to the site for our own analytical purposes. This is standard practice online, and collection is limited to information such as your IP address, the browser type and version you are using, your screen size, the URL that directed you to a site, and the length of your visit. We use this information to make the site easier to use and simpler to navigate.\r\nIf you have any questions about this policy or would like to discuss it further, please email us at neil@theroadgallery.com.','The Small Print','','publish','open','open','','thesmallprint','','','2014-12-01 16:05:54','2014-12-01 16:05:54','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?page_id=96',13,'page','',0),(108,1,'2013-12-18 01:56:45','2013-12-18 01:56:45','','slide3','','publish','closed','closed','','slide3','','','2014-02-10 02:46:13','2014-02-10 02:46:13','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?post_type=homeslider&#038;p=108',1,'homeslider','',0),(123,1,'2013-12-30 01:04:56','2013-12-30 01:04:56','Eileen Lang is an artist living and working in New York. Growing up along the lush, undulating coastline of California is the source of Lang’s tie to organic form. Training to be a ballerina cultivated an appreciation for fluid motion. An unfortunate injury redirected her creative energies towards painting, thus her work began. Today Lang lives in New York, frequenting the adjacent coastlines and feeling that same bond with the natural world. Whether moving or living, simple or complex, it is incredible how the process of nature can create such masterpieces. This serves to be the source of Lang’s motivation and inspiration. Lang’s work on photography paper utilizes the unpredictable movements of acrylic, India and Sumi ink. These paintings are inspired by the ancient Asian techniques of Suminagashi masters. Both the history, and results, are fortuitous and mystical. The message of each work is influenced and determined as inks interact on paper, and with the viewer. Individual paintings go unnamed. The intention is to invoke unique feeling and emotion which is authentic to each viewer, and unbiased. Furthermore, one cannot help but feel soothed while appreciating the simplicity and naturality of these works, reliving the way inks have mingled as they drift across paper, eventually settling in permanence.','Eileen Lang','','publish','closed','closed','','eileen-lang','','','2014-04-06 15:14:40','2014-04-06 15:14:40','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?post_type=artists&#038;p=123',10,'artists','',0),(124,1,'2013-12-30 01:14:5