27 11:48:22','2015-03-27 15:48:22','','grant_matthew conway','','inherit','open','open','','grant_matthew-conway','','','2015-03-27 11:48:22','2015-03-27 15:48:22','',2865,'http://theroadgallery.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/grant_matthew-conway.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2879,2,'2015-03-27 15:47:03','2015-03-27 19:47:03','','cory2_matthew conway','','inherit','open','open','','cory2_matthew-conway','','','2015-05-13 17:09:22','2015-05-13 21:09:22','',2820,'http://theroadgallery.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cory2_matthew-conway.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2880,2,'2015-04-02 08:46:40','2015-04-02 12:46:40','<strong>Year:</strong> 2015\r\n\r\n<strong>Height:</strong> 46\"\r\n\r\n<strong>Width:</strong> 58\"\r\n\r\n<strong>Medium:</strong> Mixed media on canvas','A Parent Piece','','publish','open','open','','a-parent-piece','','','2015-04-02 08:46:40','2015-04-02 12:46:40','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?p=2880',17,'post','',0),(2881,2,'2015-04-02 08:44:42','2015-04-02 12:44:42','','Parent Piece','','inherit','open','open','','parent-piece','','','2015-06-18 13:39:55','2015-06-18 17:39:55','',2880,'http://theroadgallery.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Parent-Piece.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2883,2,'2015-04-02 09:01:54','2015-04-02 13:01:54','Today marks the official release of a new painting by Nashville based, mixed media artist <a href=\"http://localhost/artists/taylor-thomas/\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Taylor Thomas</strong></span></a>.  <em>A Parent Piece</em> (pictured above) stands as an official beginning to a new series of paintings, <em>The Chase</em>. Below, Thomas describes the concept behind the new series and shares a poem she wrote in response to <em>A Parent Piece, </em>which gives us added insights into the intentions behind the painting.\r\n<blockquote>\"While every piece inevitably takes on a unique, visual and conceptual focus, I envision these works to function as if they were words in a [run-on] sentence. Image-by-image, they will string together a story of pursuit and attempt and reaching. Just as <em>A Parent Piece</em> responds to a painting that came before it (<em>Tower Over, Tuck Me In</em>), the next work will pick up where this one leaves off, whether in the emotive force of a shared stroke of orange, or a concept strewn through an unending line. To where will the chase continue? To whom will the story speak? And will the sentence end with another beginning, if it should choose to end at all?\"</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>A Parent Piece by Taylor Thomas</strong>\r\n\r\nI love to exercise a childlike mind: asking,\r\nrequesting, wanting--to specify\r\nmy imagination\'s musings.\r\n\r\nAt the tipping point--slipped\r\nbetween the seeking, and the receiving\r\n--are answers that rattle\r\nexpectation. I try to remember\r\n\r\nMy parent here: my pursuing,\r\ngiving, responding piece\r\n--with arms like gutter-guards\r\nand eyes that turn me\r\n\r\ninto my best, and not\r\nonto my specifications.','The Chase','A new series of work by Taylor Thomas','publish','open','open','','the-chase','','','2015-04-02 09:03:39','2015-04-02 13:03:39','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?post_type=blog&#038;p=2883',7,'blog','',0),(2884,2,'2015-04-02 08:50:46','2015-04-02 12:50:46','','Parent Piece','','inherit','open','open','','parent-piece-2','','','2015-04-02 08:50:46','2015-04-02 12:50:46','',2883,'http://theroadgallery.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Parent-Piece1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2891,2,'2015-04-03 09:11:05','2015-04-03 13:11:05','As a curator, I\'m always looking for exciting, provocative, fresh and distinctive artists with a clear point of view. Matthew Conway, who recently joined The Road Gallery as a guest artist, definitely fits the bill. Conway was born and raised in Texas and continues to reside in Austin. Having completed his BFA at the University of Texas at Austin, he has maintained his studio practice at the artist collective MASS Gallery. Additionally, he studied drawing in Florence, Italy.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_2851\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"413\"]<img class=\"wp-image-2851 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/scott_matthew-conway.jpg\" alt=\"scott_matthew conway\" width=\"413\" height=\"640\" /> scott (2015), 30\" x 22\", color pencil on toned paper[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_2830\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"427\"]<img class=\"wp-image-2830 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/adrian_matthew-conway.jpg\" alt=\"adrian_matthew conway\" width=\"427\" height=\"640\" /> adrian (2014), 30\" x 22\", color pencil on paper[/caption]\r\n\r\nIn his new series of work, Paper Dolls, Conway lays himself bare, revealing as much about himself through his drawings as he does about the subjects that posed for him. Conway does not believe in an apolitical representation of the body; every artist that chooses to render the human form reveals their values and biases. By choosing to have his straight male friends pose for his drawings, he implicates his own libidinous propensities.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_2839\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"415\"]<img class=\"wp-image-2839 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/daniel_matthew-conway.jpg\" alt=\"daniel_matthew conway\" width=\"415\" height=\"640\" /> daniel (2015), 30\" x 22\", color pencil on toned paper[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe feminist construct of the “male gaze” is redirected and queered as the heterosexual male form becomes eroticized and objectified. His work displays his desires, his humor, and his concept of beauty. Conway’s interest in gendered ephemora such as paper dolls, pin-ups, and coloring book illustrations are present in his technique and medium.\r\n\r\nWe have fifteen <a href=\"http://localhost/artists/guest-artist-matthew-conway/\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>Paper Dolls</strong></span></a> in the gallery for you to enjoy. They are all available for purchase.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_2845\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"427\"]<img class=\"wp-image-2845 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/doug_matthew-conway.jpg\" alt=\"doug_matthew conway\" width=\"427\" height=\"640\" /> doug (2014), 30\" x 22\", color pencil on toned paper[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Paper Dolls','See the new series of drawings by Matthew Conway','publish','closed','closed','','paper-dolls','','','2015-04-03 09:13:44','2015-04-03 13:13:44','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?post_type=news&#038;p=2891',5,'news','',0),(2894,2,'2015-04-04 00:36:02','2015-04-04 04:36:02','Thanks for contacting The Road Gallery. We will be in touch with you soon!','Thank You','','publish','open','open','','thank-you','','','2015-04-04 00:36:02','2015-04-04 04:36:02','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?page_id=2894',6,'page','',0),(2896,2,'2015-04-04 15:29:10','2015-04-04 19:29:10','Part of our mission at The Road Gallery is to <span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>make artwork accessible to people who love art and who want a positive experience buying art</strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">. <span style=\"color: #333333;\">Since we launched the gallery, we\'ve been listening to your feedback and continuously looking for ways to improve your on-line experience. With our mission in mind, today we launched the <span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>+ Inquire Now</strong></span> function.  This will make it much easier for you to inquire about a piece of artwork in which you are interested. All you have to do is click on the orange <span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>+ Inquire Now</strong></span> bar (shown below) when you\'ve chosen a piece you like.  </span></span></span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_2897\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"600\"]<img class=\"wp-image-2897 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-04-at-3.11.37-PM-e1428175184960.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-04-04 at 3.11.37 PM\" width=\"600\" height=\"247\" /> Step 1: Click on the orange + Inquire Now bar[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis will reveal a short, simple inquiry form.  Fill out the details and ask us any question(s) you like about the piece, including pricing information. Then click \'Submit\'. That\'s it! We\'ll respond in quick time to your inquiry. If you want information on more than one piece, pick any of the pieces you like, fill out your details on the inquiry form and include the names of the other pieces in the Message section.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_2898\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"600\"]<img class=\"wp-image-2898 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-04-at-3.12.11-PM-e1428175295978.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-04-04 at 3.12.11 PM\" width=\"600\" height=\"392\" /> Step 2: Fill out the inquiry form and click on Submit[/caption]\r\n\r\nWe hope the new form helps make our artwork even more accessible to you. If you have any other feedback for us, we\'d love to hear it. Email the gallery curator at <strong><a href=\"mailto:neil@theroadgallery.com\">neil@theroadgallery.com</a> </strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','+ Inquire Now','We\'re making things easier for you','publish','closed','closed','','inquire-now','','','2015-04-04 15:40:17','2015-04-04 19:40:17','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?post_type=news&#038;p=2896',4,'news','',0),(2897,2,'2015-04-04 15:19:28','2015-04-04 19:19:28','','Screen Shot 2015-04-04 at 3.11.37 PM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-04-04-at-3-11-37-pm','','','2015-04-04 15:19:28','2015-04-04 19:19:28','',2896,'http://theroadgallery.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-04-at-3.11.37-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2898,2,'2015-04-04 15:21:20','2015-04-04 19:21:20','','Screen Shot 2015-04-04 at 3.12.11 PM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-04-04-at-3-12-11-pm','','','2015-04-04 15:21:20','2015-04-04 19:21:20','',2896,'http://theroadgallery.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-04-at-3.12.11-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2899,2,'2015-04-04 15:26:37','2015-04-04 19:26:37','','Screen Shot 2015-04-04 at 3.08.06 PM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-04-04-at-3-08-06-pm','','','2015-04-04 15:26:37','2015-04-04 19:26:37','',2896,'http://theroadgallery.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-04-at-3.08.06-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2901,2,'2015-04-06 09:53:53','2015-04-06 13:53:53','Artist Chantal Van Houten was born and raised in the small town of Alphen aan den Rijn in the western Netherlands. With a natural inclination for art from a young age, she grew up drawing and painting while her friends were playing outside. Van Houten studied at the Academy of Media and Art in Amsterdam and after graduating in 2005, she worked for several years as a graphic designer. Yearning to express herself more freely, she left her job to focus on her art full-time.  Since then, her work has been exhibited in Austria, Germany and the Netherlands.\r\n\r\nFor Van Houten, art is about bringing emotion. There is no greater satisfaction for her than when a painting really comes alive for the viewers, sparking their imagination and touching them.  In her own words, \"the painting gives you a little tickling.\"  She gets her inspiration from the people around her, from a long walk in the park, from life and from world issues.  With her primarily figurative paintings, she wants the viewer to experience different emotions with each expression and posture they see. More specifically, she wants viewers to get closer to their feelings and emotions and rethink about what\'s really important to us as human beings living together in the world.','Guest Artist: Chantal Van Houten','','publish','closed','closed','','guest-artist-chantal-van-houten','','','2015-05-20 12:22:59','2015-05-20 16:22:59','',0,'http://theroadgallery.com/?post_type=artists&#038;p=2901',24,'artists','',